Shader and algorithm prior art
------------------------------

analog-felx implements several effects whose visual character comes from
prior art in the open-source video-effects community. Where a specific
shader or algorithm informed an implementation, the reference is credited
here even when it is in the public domain.

CC Toner — clean-room reimplementation of the Cycore CC effects bundle's
  CC Toner effect. The Cycore plugin itself is closed-source and shipped
  with After Effects; analog-felx's implementation is independent and
  derived from the publicly documented behavior. See
  effects.md § CC Toner for the algorithm breakdown.

Signal — clean-room implementation. The full ntsc-rs adapter (deferred
  follow-up F-071a) will depend on:
    ntsc-rs by valadaptive
      URL:     https://github.com/valadaptive/ntsc-rs
      License: ntscrs core crate Apache-2.0; standalone GUI app GPL-3.0
               (we depend only on the core crate).
  ntsc-rs is itself a Rust port of zhuker/ntsc (Python) which derives
  from joncampbell123/composite-video-simulator (C++). Credit to the
  full lineage.

SquintDiffusion — algorithm inspired by David van Brink's SquintDiffusion
  AE plugin ((link removed)), which is
  "Thanksware" (free for any use, attribution requested). Floyd-Steinberg
  error diffusion (1976) is the underlying algorithm and is unencumbered.
  Credit to van Brink for the directional-scan twist that gives the
  effect its recognizable look.

CRT — informed by the open-source CRT-shader community. Specific
  references read for technique (no code copied):
    crt-lottes by Timothy Lottes
      Public domain. https://github.com/libretro/glsl-shaders/blob/master/crt/shaders/crt-lottes.glsl
    Mattias Gustavsson's CRT view
      MIT OR public-domain dual. https://github.com/mattiasgustavsson/crtview
    MAME HLSL CRT shader
      BSD-3-Clause. https://docs.mamedev.org/advanced/hlsl.html
  The CRT-royale, crt-geom, and crt-easymode shaders are GPL and were
  not used as reference for code; technique only.

VHS — algorithm references:
    valadaptive/ntsc-rs (Apache-2.0 core) for signal-domain artifact
    descriptions.
    libretro/glsl-shaders/vhs/shaders/vhs.glsl (GPL — read for technique
    only, no code copied).
    Various Shadertoy entries (CC-BY-NC-SA default — read for technique
    only).
